28/09/2004
BEIJING, China -- Serbia-Montenegro's Defence Minister Prvoslav Davinic and Chinese counterpart Cao Gangchuan signed a memorandum of understanding Monday (27 September) for military co-operation. 
The agreement was sealed during Davinic's visit to Beijing.
In other news Monday, the OSCE mission to Serbia-Montenegro and the Dutch embassy in Belgrade donated equipment worth 20,000 euros to the interior ministries of the two republics. 
The donation will help reform police training in Serbia-Montenegro. 
(B92, Xinhua, OSCE Web site - 27/09/04)
